==[[w:Old English language|Old English]][[category:Words of Old English language origin]]==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*bōks''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[bok|bōk]], Old Saxon [[bok|bōk]] (Dutch [[boek]]), Old High German [[buoh]] (German [[Buch]]), Old Norse [[bók]] (Swedish [[bok]]), Gothic [[𐌱𐍉𐌺𐌰]].  The Germanic root is often taken to be related to the word for ‘beech’ (OE [[bece|bēċe]]), the wood of rune-tablets.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /bo:k/

